snippet.title: Video: How to use a protractor
snippet.description: How to use a protractor to measure angles: Line up the base line of the protractor with the side of the angle, line up the vertex of the angle with the origin of the protractor, and read the measure of the angle. Examples of measuring an acute angle, obtuse angle, a reflex angle, and an angle where you need to continue the sides before measuring.
